data.title: Delicious and busy
data.text: It's the best Tai food in Nampa. Pad Tai is usually the standard, theirs is good, not great.  Drunken noodles is the dish to order !!

data.title: Awesome lunch menu + kids meals
data.text: Small restaurant, usually always busy, nice waitresses and yummy food! Love getting their kids meal for my 3yr old but unfortunately they are not offered to go so have only ordered once. Great place to order lunch, I like to place an order over the phone and take my food to go:)

data.title: Thai food you'll crave!
data.text: Exceptional food!!!  We're picky about our Thai food but this place did not disappoint!  The food was full of flavor and had it's own twist which we loved!  It will definitely be our go-to place for Thai food.

data.title: won't go again
data.text: My husband and I went here last night.  I really do not understand how this is the number 2 restaurant in Nampa  Makes me wonder about the rest of the list.  The fresh rolls were just ok, the wine is hot, the Tom Yum is like no other we have ever had, waaay to sweet.  My meal was so sweet I  couldn't eat it and we left. I went home and had cheese and crackers.  This place was packed with people waiting but I do not understand this!  We love Thai and this was the worst we have ever had.  Very disappointing!

data.title: The food is always good!
data.text: I have tried many different things on the menu & the food is always excellent. Sometimes, it is crowded & the service a bit slow. The last 2 times I've been there, it seems like that has improved. The restaurant is small with little atmosphere, but the food makes it all worth it!

data.title: Great food and good price
data.text: Love the shrimp chips to start.  Had 8 people all ordered something different and there were no left overs on any.  Will definitely go back.

data.title: Authentic!
data.text: The food is amazing! I love Thai food and have tried most in the area. This tops them all! Everyone I have told has been very happy! The owners and chef are from Thailand. Atmosphere is warm and friendly for all ages and occasions!  They also have take-out.

data.title: Very Tasty
data.text: Visiting here from CA and this restaurant has great food. We ordered the drunken fried rice and the drunken noodle extra spicy ...great flavor. We will be back for more!!

data.title: Dinner
data.text: Geral food very traditional dishes! Ambiance isn't all that great but food is really good and not overpriced. If you just want some good Thai food to eat and don't mind the plate lunch setting this is your best choice in Nampa

data.title: Great place
data.text: Great food and service. It was our 7th visit and every one has been excellent. We will go back often. Just wish it was closer.

data.title: Authentic and delicious Thai food!
data.text:
Chef Pong never disappoints! For lunch you will be served a green salad or a delicious home-made soup along with your lunch special. At night they serve shrimp chips with a spicy dip. 

Some of our favorite dishes include Black Pepper Chicken, Pad Thai, Garlic Noodle, Teriyaki Chicken, Tom Kah Gai soup, Thailand Fried Rice with chicken and Thai Basil. Don't forget to order a Thai Tea as well! 

Always great service! Sometimes you have to wait for a table if you go during the busy lunch hour....because the food is just that delicious!

data.title: Great Thai food in Idaho
data.text:
Quick, prompt, friendly, clean and busy are five words that describe this restaurant.  Our group of six visited here for lunch. Every table was full.  Every time one party left the restaurant, the table was cleaned well and quickly, and someone new was seated at the table. It seemed that only one party had to wait for about 5 minutes for a table.

The food was as close to authentic as we have had in the USA. Thai cooks and servers work here at a brisk pace with quality in the foods, nice plate presentations, and a more than sufficient quantity of food.

We asked to be served "Thai style", meaning family style, and they gladly made the adjustment to this type of service. This made it easy for our friends to share the different items that were ordered from the menu.

Prices are reasonable, not cheap but not expensive either. When ever we visit Nampa in the future, we will be sure to make this restaurant one of our first choices for a meal out.

As for the spiciness of the meals, they kitchen handled both a desire for non-spicy and normal spicy meals with ease and with accuracy.

data.title: ❤️
data.text: Yummy food. Great service. Try the Thai tea or coffee! Can be busy during weekend dinner, but going for lunch is well worth it!

data.title: Thai Food
data.text: Best Thai food since leaving Southern CA! Who knew  Nampa would have such great Thai. Small restaurant but great service.

data.title: Various times/days
data.text: Absolutely outstanding food and service every time we have been there. JP Thailand Express is really popular, so try to get there early. There may be a line but it's well worth waiting for!

data.title: Great Thai food!
data.text: I've been here twice and really enjoyed it both times.  So many wonderful dishes to choose from.  Lots of variety & great flavors!

data.title: Great food and prices
data.text:
I have eaten here a number of times and have not been disappointed.

One word of caution.......they are very busy at lunch time, best to go before 12 or after one.

data.title: Best Restaurant in Nampa—Hands Down! Among the Top in the Treasure Valley!
data.text: You can't to wrong with this small restaurant! The Panang Curry is a favorite. Hard to get a seat on weekends; however, top quality Thai food. The quality is far better than the other Thai restaurant in Nampa, high quality food keeps customers coming back and the other restaurant should take some hints. We order out at Thailand Express at least a couple times per week (lunch or dinner).

data.title: Amazing as always
data.text: So fresh and delicious! My kids' favorite are the shrimp chips. Never had a bad experience. So friendly. We love Thailand Express!

data.title: Amazing food (Again)!
data.text:
This is not an old yucky oriental restaurant.  It is modern, clean and tastefully decorated.  I visited for my 3rd time and came with a reservation.  As promised in our last review, we ordered one of the famous Thai soups this time.  We were disappointed.  It did taste good, but it didn’t taste like it is supposed to taste.  I recently visited Thailand and their Tom Yam has pretty much the same flavor everywhere you go.  This was missing something.
    * Tom Yam Soup:  5 out of 10 (Good but not authentic).
Here’s the rest of what we ordered this time:
    * Chicken Satay: 10 out of 10
    * Yellow curry fried rice: 10 out of 10 (Not a dish I normally order) 
    * Som Tam (papaya): 10 out of 10 (Asked for no dried shrimp)
From our experience last time:
    * Chicken Satay: 10 out of 10
    * Phat Thai: 8 out of 10 (but my wife didn't like it??)
    * Pat prick pao: 10 out of 10 (Not a dish I normally order) 
    * Laab chicken: 10 out of 10
    * Som Tam (papaya): 10 out of 10
Normally we get it without the little shrimp. We forgot this time but it was still incredible.
    * Nam Tok: 5 out of 10
The last 2 times we visited, we had to wait quite a while to be seated.  The restaurant is very busy.  We were a party of 9 and were given an automatic 18% gratuity on our bill.  I’m cheap and usually don’t give that much unless I really like the place.  I did reserve ahead and came in a large group, but it still rubbed me a little wrong being given a forced, not suggested, tip (That’s the only reason I’m taking off 1 star).  I do plan to visit again.  I like to tip at 20%, or more, if the prices are decent and the food/service are really good.  This time they only got their 18.
